sentences: Richard "Rick" Blackburn (16 November, 1942 – 30 November, 2012) was a Nashville music executive.
Blackburn was known for hiring top artists like Ricky Van Shelton and George Jones and for dropping Johnny Cash off at Nashville Records around 1985 or 1986.
He retired from the music industry in the 1990s and died in his Tennessee home of kidney failure.
